pater. Gods and beneficent powers are often so styled. The title is even extended to great rivers—the Tiber (Verg. Georg. iv. 369) and the Nile (Tib. i. 7. 23). Compare also ‘pater Ennius' (Horace and Propertius), like our Dan Chaucer (Dan=Dominus). When pateris used in this way, the idea of majesty predominates over that of age.
